cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with problems related to computational geometry and discrete mathematics, specifically set cover and hitting set problems for polytopes in $\R^3$. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which is related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
